SIMPLE: spotlight
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spotlight
<hw>Spot"light`</hw> <pr>(sp⟦ocr⟧t"l⟦imac⟧t`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The projected spot or circle of light used to
illuminate brilliantly a single person or object or group on the stage,
leaving the rest of the stage more or less unilluminated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>hence, conspicuous public notice.</def> <mark>[Cant
or Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A lighting apparatus designed to throw an intense
beam of light onto a small area.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spot stroke</ent>⟦br⟧
